{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1190,"text":"I'm going to start\nby asking you a question:"},{"time":3697,"text":"Is anyone familiar\nwith the blue algae problem?"},{"time":7776,"text":"Okay, so most of you are."},{"time":9825,"text":"I think we can all agree\nit's a serious issue."},{"time":12871,"text":"Nobody wants to drink\nblue algae-contaminated water,"},{"time":16763,"text":"or swim in a blue algae-infested lake."},{"time":21328,"text":"Right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":22703,"text":"I hope you won't be disappointed,"},{"time":24779,"text":"but today,\nI won't be talking about blue algae."},{"time":27985,"text":"Instead,\nI'll be talking about the main cause"},{"time":31810,"text":"at the root of this issue,"},{"time":34775,"text":"which I will be referring to as\nthe phosphorus crisis."},{"time":38170,"text":"Why have I chosen to talk to you\nabout the phosphorus crisis today?"},{"time":42078,"text":"For the simple reason\nthat nobody else is talking about it."},{"time":45337,"text":"And by the end of my presentation,\nI hope that the general public"},{"time":49604,"text":"will be more aware of this crisis\nand this issue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":54170,"text":"Now, the problem is that if I ask,"},{"time":57534,"text":"why do we find ourselves\nin this situation with blue algae?"},{"time":60588,"text":"The answer is\nthat it comes from how we farm."},{"time":64262,"text":"We use fertilizers in our farming,\nchemical fertilizers."},{"time":68696,"text":"Why do we use chemical fertilizers\nin agriculture?"},{"time":71103,"text":"Basically, to help plants grow\nand to produce a better yield."},{"time":76343,"text":"The issue is that this is set to engender"},{"time":78787,"text":"an environmental problem\nthat is without precedent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":83471,"text":"Before going further, let me give you\na crash course in plant biology."},{"time":87037,"text":"So, what does a plant need\nin order to grow?"},{"time":89502,"text":"A plant, quite simply,\nneeds light, it needs CO2,"},{"time":94052,"text":"but even more importantly,\nit needs nutrients,"},{"time":97667,"text":"which it draws from the soil."},{"time":101282,"text":"Several of these nutrients\nare essential chemical elements:"},{"time":104897,"text":"phosphorus, nitrogen and calcium."},{"time":107943,"text":"So, the plant’s roots will extract\nthese resources."}]},{"cues":[{"time":112672,"text":"Today I'll be focusing on a major problem\nthat is linked to phosphorus."},{"time":116536,"text":"Why phosphorus in particular?"},{"time":118223,"text":"Because it is\nthe most problematic chemical element."},{"time":121572,"text":"By the end of my presentation,\nyou will have seen"},{"time":124693,"text":"what these problems are,\nand where we are today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":128839,"text":"Phosphorus is a chemical element"},{"time":131772,"text":"that is essential to life.\nThis is a very important point."},{"time":135165,"text":"I’d like everyone to understand precisely\nwhat the phosphorus issue is."},{"time":138816,"text":"Phosphorus is a key component\nin several molecules,"},{"time":142988,"text":"in many of our molecules of life."},{"time":145641,"text":"Experts in the field will know"},{"time":147634,"text":"that cellular communication\nis phosphorus-based --"},{"time":150597,"text":"phosphorylation, dephosphorylation."},{"time":153221,"text":"Cell membranes are phosphorus-based:\nThese are called phospholipids."},{"time":158822,"text":"The energy in all living things,\nATP, is phosphorus-based."},{"time":163572,"text":"And more importantly still,\nphosphorus is a key component of DNA,"},{"time":170455,"text":"something everyone is familiar with,\nand which is shown in this image."},{"time":175055,"text":"DNA is our genetic heritage."},{"time":178339,"text":"It is extremely important, and once again,\nphosphorus is a key player."}]},{"cues":[{"time":183360,"text":"Now, where do we find this phosphorus?"},{"time":187308,"text":"As humans, where do we find it?"},{"time":190869,"text":"As I explained earlier,"},{"time":192358,"text":"plants extract phosphorus\nfrom the soil, through water."},{"time":197147,"text":"So, we humans get it\nfrom the things we eat:"},{"time":200722,"text":"plants, vegetables, fruits,"},{"time":203397,"text":"and also from eggs, meat and milk."},{"time":206912,"text":"It’s true that some humans\neat better than others."},{"time":209969,"text":"Some are happier than others."},{"time":212605,"text":"And now, looking at this picture,\nwhich speaks for itself,"},{"time":217076,"text":"we see modern agriculture,"},{"time":218892,"text":"which I also refer to\nas intensive agriculture."},{"time":222448,"text":"Intensive agriculture is based\non the use of chemical fertilizers."},{"time":226904,"text":"Without them,\nwe would not manage to produce enough"},{"time":229932,"text":"to feed the world's population."},{"time":232960,"text":"Speaking of humans, there are currently\n7 billion of us on Earth."},{"time":236738,"text":"In less than 40 years,\nthere will be 9 billion of us."},{"time":239864,"text":"And the question is a simple one:\nDo we have enough phosphorus"},{"time":243254,"text":"to feed our future generations?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":247134,"text":"So, in order to understand these issues,\nwhere do we find our phosphorus?"},{"time":251216,"text":"Let me explain."},{"time":252997,"text":"But first, let’s just suppose"},{"time":255844,"text":"that we are using\n100 percent of a given dose of phosphorus."},{"time":261690,"text":"Only 15 percent of this 100 percent goes to the plant.\nEighty-five percent is lost."},{"time":270278,"text":"It goes into the soil,\nending its journey in the lakes,"},{"time":273947,"text":"resulting in lakes with extra phosphorus,\nwhich leads to the blue algae problem."},{"time":277673,"text":"So, you’ll see there’s a problem here,\nsomething that is illogical."},{"time":281411,"text":"A hundred percent of the phosphorus is used,\nbut only 15 percent goes to the plant."},{"time":285850,"text":"You’re going to tell me it’s wasteful."},{"time":288274,"text":"Yes, it is. What is worse\nis that it is very expensive."},{"time":292401,"text":"Nobody wants to throw their money\nout the window,"},{"time":295783,"text":"but unfortunately\nthat's what is happening here."},{"time":298513,"text":"Eighty percent of each dose of phosphorus is lost."},{"time":303049,"text":"Modern agriculture\ndepends on phosphorus."},{"time":308701,"text":"And because in order to get 15 percent of it\nto the plant, all the rest is lost,"},{"time":313300,"text":"we have to add more and more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":315221,"text":"Now, where will we get\nthis phosphorus from?"},{"time":319135,"text":"Basically, we get it out of mines."},{"time":322989,"text":"This is the cover\nof an extraordinary article"},{"time":325516,"text":"published in Nature in 2009,"},{"time":327273,"text":"which really launched the discussion\nabout the phosphorus crisis."},{"time":330460,"text":"Phosphorus, a nutrient essential to life,\nwhich is becoming increasingly scarce,"},{"time":335423,"text":"yet nobody is talking about it."},{"time":337246,"text":"And everyone agrees:\nPoliticians and scientists are in agreement"},{"time":343110,"text":"that we are headed\nfor a phosphorus crisis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":345451,"text":"What you are seeing here\nis an open-pit mine in the U.S.,"},{"time":348899,"text":"and to give you an idea\nof the dimensions of this mine,"},{"time":352000,"text":"if you look in the top right-hand corner,\nthe little crane you can see,"},{"time":355554,"text":"that is a giant crane."},{"time":357369,"text":"So that really puts it into perspective."},{"time":360403,"text":"So, we get phosphorus from mines."},{"time":362601,"text":"And if I make a comparison with oil,"},{"time":365809,"text":"there’s an oil crisis, we talk about it,\nwe talk about global warming,"},{"time":369180,"text":"yet we never mention\nthe phosphorus crisis."},{"time":371204,"text":"To come back to the oil problem,\noil is something we can replace."},{"time":375406,"text":"We can use biofuels, or solar power,"},{"time":379768,"text":"or hydropower,\nbut phosphorus is an essential element,"},{"time":383532,"text":"indispensable to life,\nand we can’t replace it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":389106,"text":"What is the current state\nof the world's phosphorus reserves?"},{"time":392769,"text":"This graph gives you a rough idea\nof where we are today."},{"time":396880,"text":"The black line represents predictions\nfor phosphorus reserves."},{"time":401531,"text":"In 2030, we’ll reach the peak."},{"time":404155,"text":"By the end of this century,\nit will all be gone."},{"time":407661,"text":"The dotted line shows where we are today."},{"time":411976,"text":"As you can see, they meet in 2030,\nI’ll be retired by then."},{"time":416658,"text":"But we are indeed heading\nfor a major crisis,"},{"time":420227,"text":"and I’d like people to become aware\nof this problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":424089,"text":"Do we have a solution?"},{"time":426449,"text":"What are we to do?\nWe are faced with a paradox."},{"time":430531,"text":"Less and less phosphorus\nwill be available."},{"time":433118,"text":"By 2050 there will be 9 billion of us,"},{"time":436484,"text":"and according to\nthe U.N. Food and Agriculture Organization,"},{"time":443098,"text":"we will need to produce twice as much food\nin 2050 than we do today."},{"time":447841,"text":"So, we will have less phosphorus,\nbut we'll need to produce more food."},{"time":452141,"text":"What should we do?"},{"time":454199,"text":"It truly is a paradoxical situation."},{"time":457029,"text":"Do we have a solution,\nor an alternative"},{"time":459777,"text":"which will allow us to optimize\nphosphorus use?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":462745,"text":"Remember that 80 percent is destined to be lost."},{"time":468365,"text":"The solution I'm offering today is one\nthat has existed for a very long time,"},{"time":475669,"text":"even before plants existed on Earth,"},{"time":478407,"text":"and it's a microscopic mushroom\nthat is very mysterious,"},{"time":481885,"text":"very simple,\nand yet also extremely complex."},{"time":485933,"text":"I've been fascinated by this little mushroom\nfor over 16 years now."},{"time":490621,"text":"It has led me to further my research"},{"time":494466,"text":"and to use it as a model\nfor my laboratory research."}]},{"cues":[{"time":497836,"text":"This mushroom exists in symbiosis\nwith the roots."},{"time":501550,"text":"By symbiosis, I mean a bidirectional\nand mutually beneficial association"},{"time":506937,"text":"which is also called mycorrhiza."},{"time":512085,"text":"This slide illustrates the elements\nof a mycorrhiza."},{"time":515142,"text":"You’re looking at the root of wheat,"},{"time":517407,"text":"one of the world’s most important plants."},{"time":521501,"text":"Normally, a root will find phosphorus\nall by itself."},{"time":524340,"text":"It will go in search of phosphorus,"},{"time":526372,"text":"but only within the one millimeter\nwhich surrounds it."},{"time":530044,"text":"Beyond one millimeter,\nthe root is ineffective."},{"time":533119,"text":"It cannot go further\nin its search for phosphorus."},{"time":535444,"text":"Now, imagine this tiny,\nmicroscopic mushroom."},{"time":538180,"text":"It grows much faster,"},{"time":540441,"text":"and is much better designed\nto seek out phosphorus."},{"time":543237,"text":"It can go beyond\nthe root’s one-millimeter scope"},{"time":546616,"text":"to seek out phosphorus."}]},{"cues":[{"time":548703,"text":"I haven’t invented anything at all;"},{"time":550759,"text":"it's a biotechnology that has existed\nfor 450 million years."},{"time":554257,"text":"And over time, this mushroom\nhas evolved and adapted to seek out"},{"time":558170,"text":"even the tiniest trace of phosphorus,\nand to put it to use,"},{"time":561663,"text":"to make it available to the plant."},{"time":564716,"text":"What you’re seeing here,\nin the real world, is a carrot root,"},{"time":569289,"text":"and the mushroom\nwith its very fine filaments."},{"time":571920,"text":"Looking closer,\nwe can see that this mushroom"},{"time":574327,"text":"is very gentle in its penetration."},{"time":576414,"text":"It will proliferate\nbetween the root's cells,"},{"time":580103,"text":"eventually penetrating a cell"},{"time":583596,"text":"and starting to form\na typical arbuscular structure,"},{"time":588600,"text":"which will considerably increase\nthe exchange interface"},{"time":593477,"text":"between the plant and the mushroom."},{"time":596036,"text":"And it is through this structure\nthat mutual exchanges will occur."},{"time":599481,"text":"It’s a win-win trade:"},{"time":601117,"text":"I give you phosphorus, and you feed me."},{"time":603992,"text":"True symbiosis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":608602,"text":"Now let's add a mycorrhiza plant"},{"time":611370,"text":"into the diagram I used earlier."},{"time":614630,"text":"And instead of using a 100 percent dose,\nI’m going to reduce it to 25 percent."},{"time":619707,"text":"You’ll see that of this 25 percent,\nmost will benefit the plant,"},{"time":624681,"text":"more than 90 percent."},{"time":626237,"text":"A very small amount of phosphorus\nwill remain in the soil."},{"time":629817,"text":"That's completely natural."},{"time":633577,"text":"What's more is that in certain cases,\nwe don't even need to add phosphorus."}]},{"cues":[{"time":637448,"text":"If you recall the graphs\nI showed you earlier,"},{"time":639860,"text":"85 percent of phosphorus is lost in the soil,"},{"time":643081,"text":"and the plants are unable to access it."},{"time":646326,"text":"Even though it is present in the soil,\nit is in insoluble form."},{"time":650134,"text":"The plant is only able to seek out\nsoluble forms."},{"time":653144,"text":"The mushroom is capable\nof dissolving this insoluble form"},{"time":656956,"text":"and making it available\nfor the plant to use."},{"time":660397,"text":"To further support my argument,\nhere is a picture that speaks for itself."},{"time":663948,"text":"These are trials\nin a field of sorghum."},{"time":667836,"text":"On the left side, you see the yield\nproduced using conventional agriculture,"},{"time":672348,"text":"with a 100 percent phosphorus dose."},{"time":675090,"text":"On the other side,\nthe dose was reduced to 50 percent,"},{"time":678303,"text":"and just look at the yield."},{"time":679836,"text":"With only a half-dose,\nwe achieved a better yield."}]},{"cues":[{"time":685417,"text":"This is to show you\nthat this method works."},{"time":690247,"text":"And in some cases, in Cuba,\nMexico and India,"},{"time":694816,"text":"the dose can be reduced to 25 percent,\nand in several other cases,"},{"time":698103,"text":"there's no need to add\nany phosphorus at all,"},{"time":700257,"text":"because the mushrooms are so well adapted"},{"time":702701,"text":"to finding phosphorus\nand drawing it from the soil."},{"time":705897,"text":"This is an example of soy production\nin Canada."},{"time":711735,"text":"Mycorrhiza was used in one field\nbut not in the other."},{"time":719347,"text":"And here, where blue indicates a better yield,\nand yellow a weaker yield."},{"time":728763,"text":"The black rectangle is the plot"},{"time":731586,"text":"from which the mycorrhiza was added."},{"time":733969,"text":"In other words, as I already said,\nI have invented nothing."},{"time":737337,"text":"Mycorrhiza has existed\nfor 450 million years,"},{"time":740087,"text":"and it has even helped\nmodern-day plant species to diversify."}]},{"cues":[{"time":744346,"text":"So, this it isn't something\nthat is still undergoing lab tests."},{"time":748905,"text":"Mycorrhiza exists, it works,"},{"time":751321,"text":"it's produced at an industrial scale\nand commercialized worldwide."},{"time":755760,"text":"The problem is\nthat people are not aware of it."},{"time":759070,"text":"People like food producers and farmers\nare still not aware of this problem."},{"time":763066,"text":"We have a technology that works,"},{"time":765694,"text":"and one that, if used correctly,\nwill alleviate some of the pressure"},{"time":772791,"text":"we are putting\non the world's phosphorus reserves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":777214,"text":"In conclusion,\nI am a scientist and a dreamer."},{"time":782368,"text":"I'm passionate about this topic."},{"time":784127,"text":"So if you were to ask me\nwhat my retirement dream is,"},{"time":787415,"text":"which will be at the moment we reach\nthat phosphorus peak,"},{"time":790241,"text":"it would be that we use one label,\n\"Made with mycorrhiza,\""},{"time":794197,"text":"and that my children and grandchildren"},{"time":797107,"text":"buy products bearing that label too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":800115,"text":"Thank you for your attention."}]},{"cues":[{"time":801815,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}